        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We select the total bandwidth of about 1500 km/s and the resolution of about 25 km/s. This choice will give us from ~2 to ~12 spectral channels per line which is adequate.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The source consists of two main components separated by about 4". Therefore we chose the largest angular scale of 5". Our goal is just the detection of possible emission from these components and the angular resolution of 1" will be adequate.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The CO and [C II] line widths in this object are about 300 km/s. The HeH+ line width can be significantly different since the formation and excitation conditions are different. We estimate the sensitivity for the probably minimal expected line width of 50 km/s. 
If we assume the expected line intensity about the same as for our tentative line in SDSS J114816.64+525150.3, the required rms noise for 5sigma detection is about 1.5 mJy at 50 km/s resolution. However we aim at the better sensitivity of 0.3 mJy. It will be adequate for the CO(18-17) line, too.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
